{"lemma": "غُول", "slug": "غُول", "root": "غ.#.ل", "root_slug": "غ-_-ل", "root_link": "/words/roots/غ-_-ل", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun_prop", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "غُول", "root": "غول", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 6}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n32655", "n32656"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%84"}}, "translations": {"en": "ape", "fa": "میمون", "ur": "بندر", "tr": "maymun", "id": "kera", "bn": "বানর", "es": "mono", "fr": "singe", "de": "Affe", "ru": "обезьяна", "zh": "猿"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ape, orangutan", "tags": ["obsolete"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ghoul, desert demon"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "demon, jinn, goblin, monster"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ogre, cannibal, troll, oni, giant"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "calamity, disaster"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "taking away, snatching, seizing, grabbing"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From the root غ و ل (ḡ w l), related to غَالَ (ḡāla, “to seize”).\nCompare Sumerian [script needed] (gula, “great”).\n\nVerbal noun of غَالَ (ḡāla, “to snatch, to grab, to take away”)."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n32655", "headword_ar": "غَوْلٌ", "root": "gwl", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Far extent"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a desert, or waterless desert; (S, O, TA;) because it destroys him who passes along in it: (S, TA:) or of a land; because it casts away the travellers, or wayfarers, causes them to fall, or drop down, and removes them far away: and accord. to Lh, it is said of a land when one journeys in it without stopping. (TA.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^aboEada gawola h`*ihi AlA^aroDi", "text_ar": "مَا اَبْعَدَ غَوْلَ هٰذِهِ الاَرْضِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How far is the extent of this land!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~ahaA labaEiydapu Algawoli", "text_ar": "اـِنَّهَا لَبَعِيدَةُ الغَوْلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily it is far in extent"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (ISh, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroDN *aAtu", "text_ar": "اَرْضٌ ذَاتُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gawolK", "text_ar": "غَوْلٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A land far extending, though in the view of the eye of little extent:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IKh, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gay~ilN", "text_ar": "غَيِّلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to land is said to have the same meaning. (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gyl", "text_ar": "غيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^agowaAlu AlA^aroDi", "text_ar": "اَغْوَالُ الاَرْضِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AgwAl", "text_ar": "اغوال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is app. pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gawolN", "text_ar": "غَوْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The extremities of the land."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AimoraA^apN *aAtu gawolK", "text_ar": "اِمْرَاَةٌ ذَاتُ غَوْلٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A tall woman."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) See 1, last sentence but two. [And see also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gay~ilapN", "text_ar": "غَيِّلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gay~ilN", "text_ar": "غَيِّلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gyl", "text_ar": "غيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b3-  ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nAqp gwl AlnjA='", "text_ar": "ناقة غول النجا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a phrase mentioned without any indication of the meaning in the TA: perhaps"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAqapu gawoli Aln~ajaA='i", "text_ar": "نَاقَةُ غَوْلِ النَّجَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A she-camel of an exceeding degree of swiftness."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]       -A2-  In the saying in the Kur [xxxvii. 46],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA fiyhaA gawolN", "text_ar": "لَا فِيهَا غَوْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [referring to the wine of Paradise,] it means The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "evil result of headache;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because it is said in another place, [lvi. 19,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA yuSad~aEuwna EanohaA", "text_ar": "لَا يُصَدَّعُونَ عَنْهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O, TA:) or it [there] means [simply]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "headache:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "intoxication:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) thus some expl. it as used in that instance: (TA:) or, as expl. by AO, it there means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "privation of the intellectual faculties."}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2311}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "guwlN", "text_ar": "غُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", latter half. ―         -b3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Distress, trouble,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "molestation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) thus expl. by some as used in the Kur ubi suprà. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Unfaithfulness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unfaithful acting."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b5-  ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ataY gawolFA gaAy^ilapF", "text_ar": "اَتَى غَوْلًا غَايِلَةً", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He did a cunning, bad, action."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)       -A3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Much earth."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K.) Hence the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gawolFA mina Alr~amoli", "text_ar": "غَوْلًا مِنَ الرَّمْلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A large quantity of sand,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] in a verse of Lebeed. (S, O.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A collection of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the trees called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaloH", "text_ar": "طَلْح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with which nothing participates."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A low,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "depressed, part of the earth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of land."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "TA", "IKh", "O", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n32656", "headword_ar": "غُولٌ", "root": "gwl", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A kind of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goblin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "demon, devil,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "jinnee, which, the Arabs assert, appears to men in the desert, assuming various forms, causing them to wander from the way, and destroying them;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JM, and TA * on the authority of IAth;) but this the Prophet denied, saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA guwla", "text_ar": "لَا غُولَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; by which, however, accord. to some, he did not mean to deny the existence of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gwl", "text_ar": "غول"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but only the assertion of the Arabs respecting its assuming various forms and its being able to cause any one to go astray: (IAth, JM, * TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siEolaApN", "text_ar": "سِعْلَاةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]: or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a sort of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siEolaAp", "text_ar": "سِعْلَاة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O, Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a male jinnee;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the female being called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siEolaAp", "text_ar": "سِعْلَاة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Abu-l-Wefee ElAarábee, TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^agowaAlN", "text_ar": "اَغْوَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "giylaAnN", "text_ar": "غِيلَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "giwalapN", "text_ar": "غِوَلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (O, TA:) and it signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an enchantress of the jinn:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a demon,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "devil, that eats men:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(En-Nadr, O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any jinnee,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "devil,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "animal of prey, that destroys a man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain beast,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "terrible"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in appearance"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having tusks,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fangs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "seen by the Arabs, and known by them; and killed by Taäbbata Sharrà:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as varies in form"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "appearance, of the enchanters"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the jinn;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA;) on his doing which, as is said in a trad., one should hastily utter the call to prayer, to prevent his mischief by the mention of God: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anything by reason of which the intellect departs;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gawolN", "text_ar": "غَوْلٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anything that takes a man unexpectedly and destroys him:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb:) [whence] one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlgaDabu guwlu AlHilomi", "text_ar": "الغَضَبُ غُولُ الحِلْمِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anger"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is that which"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "destroys,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "does away with, forbearance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "clemency."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Destruction:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a cause thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "death;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the decree of death."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) See 1, second sentence. ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A calamity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "misfortune;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaAy^ilapN", "text_ar": "غَايِلَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) of which latter the pl. in this sense is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gawaAy^ilu", "text_ar": "غَوَايِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (K, * TA;) thus mentioned by Ks. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A serpent:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^agowaAlN", "text_ar": "اَغْوَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) accord. to Az, the Arabs call serpents"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^agowaAl", "text_ar": "اَغْوَال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and thus this word is said to mean in the verse of Imra-el-Keys,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "liyaqotulaniY waAlma$orafiY~u muDaAjiEiY\n                      \n                     \n                        wamasonuwnapN zuroqN kaA^anoyaAbi A^agowaAli"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "To slay me, while the Meshrefee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "sword"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was my bedfellow, and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so were"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sharpened, polished"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "arrowheads,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like the fangs of serpents"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (O, TA: *) but AHát says that this is meant as an exaggeration: (TA:) and it is said that the poet here means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "devils."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "O", "Msb", "K", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}